# Floral-V1

## Dash Application

Activate the virtual environment and launch the interactive planner with:

```bash
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m floral_v1.app.app
```

This starts the Dash UI, which walks through the full pipeline:
`size_gensets -> build_site_model -> place_assets -> optimize_hybrid -> verify_availability -> run_des -> export`.

## Smoke Scenarios

Run the reference scenarios directly from the CLI:

```bash
python -m floral_v1.scripts.smoke_pipeline          # demo defaults
python -m floral_v1.scripts.smoke_pipeline small    # ~3 MW campus
python -m floral_v1.scripts.smoke_pipeline large    # ~10 MW campus
```

Each scenario executes the full integrated pipeline and prints a concise summary of genset sizing, hybrid design, analytical availability, and DES metrics.

## Tests

Execute the regression tests with:

```bash
pytest floral_v1/tests
```

## Legacy Folders

`DESModel/`, `digital_twin_ryan/`, and `siteplan-visuals/` remain in the repository for reference, but the production code path runs entirely inside `floral_v1/`.
